      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those who advocate for a genetic argument often point to twin studies or family resemblance as evidence. They claim that because identical twins exhibit more similar IQ scores regardless of their environments, genetics plays a crucial role. They also suggest that some racial groups might have different genetic predispositions for intelligence. They believe these innate differences affect educational outcomes and socioeconomic positions, inherently favoring one group over others. This argument downplays the impact of social inequality and educational disparities.",
