      "role": "user",
      "content": "right, but if people are saying those differences are actually biological, does that imply there's a predictable hierarchy or a ranking of groups based on those averages? like, if you look at the actual datasets, do they show a clear pattern of which groups tend to score higher or lower? just trying to understand the actual implications of those claims.",
